items.title: Dollar Rethink Is Pushing Emerging World to Sell More Euro Debt
items.description: (Bloomberg) -- Emerging-market borrowers are tapping the euro bond market at the fastest pace in over a decade, capitalizing on the rising demand for diversification away from the US dollar.
